..TEXT:
|la scorta mia... m'offerse~: Virgil draws near to
Dante and offers him his shoulder, that he may rest his hand on
it and be guided, like a blind man.  This does not mean that
Virgil himself can see in the smoke.  In fact, the closing verse
of the preceding canto has it that the smoke "took from us our
sight."  Moreover, the spirits that are here being purged of
wrath are surely blinded by the smoke.  But Virgil as a wise
guide has a way of "seeing" that is not purely physical and
accordingly can lead Dante on around the terrace.
..TCHR:
527
