..TEXT:
|del mondo seppi~: "I knew [the ways] of the world."
The reader will remember Ulysses, who sought to become "del mondo
esperto / e de li vizi umani e del valore" (^Inf.~ XXVI, 98-
99).  |valore~: Virtue in general, as in Ulysses' words and also
in Guido del Duca's in ^Purg.~ XIV, 37.
