..TEXT:
|pur come se... necessitate~: "As if they (the
heavens) moved everything with them by necessity" (i.e., with an
absolute determinism).  See Dante's ^Epist.~ XI, 4: "Et, quod
horribilius est, quod astronomi quidam et crude prophetantes
necessarium asserunt quod, male usi libertate arbitrii, eligere
maluistis."  ("And, what is more horrible, certain astronomers,
crudely prophesying, declare that to be of necessity which in
truth ye, making ill use of the liberty of the will, have rather
chosen.")
