|mossa da lieto fattore... trastulla~: The joy of
the Creator, in creating the soul He so fondly contemplates first
in idea, is communicated to it as a natural inclination, so that
it always seeks (turns to) that which can give it joy.  See
^Purg.~ XVIII, 55-60, and in general the argument of ^Purg.~ XVII
and XVIII.
