|prima che Federigo avesse briga~: The expression ^aver
briga~ views the matter from the standpoint of the emperor.  In the
struggle of the papacy against Frederick II, last of the emperors
according to Dante (see n. to vs. 98), the papacy took up the sword,
which it should not have done.
