..TEXT:
|or pu@o sicuramente... d'appressarsi~: Anyone who,
because he is evil and degenerate, would seek to avoid the
company of good men may now pass through Lombardy without risk of
encountering any good men.  For the construction ^per~ with agent, see
^Inf.~ I, 126.  ^Lasciare~ in this use, meaning "to avoid" or "to
eschew," is commonly found in early Italian.  Compare the judgment on
this region with that on Romagna in ^Purg.~ XIV, 91-96.
